<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 9200, 9300 AND 9400 SERIES -
        INSPECTION AND MAINTENANCE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSPECTION AND MAINTENANCE</title>
        <para>Inspect the clutch control components and operation at the lubrication intervals, or at least once yearly.
            Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s11010k_6.xml" xrefid="hl1101002">LUBRICATION
                <xref refid="hl1101002"/>
            </hotlnk>
            .
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect for worn or damaged parts. Look for worn pins or excessively worn holes in levers
                and clevis yokes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate and adjust the clutch linkage when installing new parts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the length of clutch pedal free travel; if it is not correct, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s11010k_5.xml" xrefid="hl1101001">ADJUSTMENTS
                    <xref refid="hl1101001"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
